    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-11T06:09:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-11T06:09:00-05:00" n="378"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119/2668: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Grand <persName type="from">Duchess Marie Adelaide</persName>
                        of Luxemburg to President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Translation]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-11T11:28:00+00:19"
                            >November 11, 1918—11:28 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to solemn protests of Luxemburg people and their Grand Duchess against
                    foreign occupation, I pray the President kindly to intervene to save the Grand
                    Duchy from the passage of German troops and to protect, at the peace
                    negotiations, the rights and interests of the Luxemburg free and independent
                    small people.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marie Adelaide</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
